race.comment: SHOW BUSINESS (7) dominated a mare's Class 1 over this distance at Kembla two back. Started favourite at Canterbury on the back of that effort but was a shade disappointing although early interference didn't help. Worth another chance back in this company. PUERTO BANUS (2) enjoyed a drop in grade and a 32-day let-up when an eye-catching second last time out over today's course and distance. Perfectly drawn and this doesn't look quite as testing so he is a huge chance. EQUILIBRIST (3) gets a pass mark for his midfield finish first-up over 1250m at the Kensington track. Yet to place in four first-up runs but has better second-up stats so a spike in form is anticipated. CAN'T TOUCH THIS (8) has led all the way to win two of her last three, both over six furlongs and most recently at Gosford. Rarely puts two good runs together but don't take her lightly. ORYX (6) is best of the others over a slightly longer trip today at the third run back.
